Lecture1 Intro, Hello World Java

Phase1 基础java语法（1-4周）（HW0.proj0.proj1）
Phase2 数据结构（5-10周）（HW1.HW2.Proj2）
Phase3 算法及软件工程（10-14周）（Proj3）

Java基础语法规则：
*helloword.java
1.All code in java must be part of a class.
2.We delimit the beginning and end of segments of code with{}.
3.All statements in java must end in a semi-colon.
4.For code to run we need public static void main(String[] args).

*hellonumber.java
5.Before java variables can be used,they must be declared.
6.Java variables must have a specific type.
7.Java variable types can never change.
8.Types are verified before the code runs,if there are type issues,the code will not compile.

*largerdemo.java
9.To declare a function in java,use "public static"(for today).
10.All parameters of a function must have a type,and the function itself must have a return type.
11.All functions must be part of a class.In programming language terminology,a function that is part of a class is called a "method",so all functions in java are methods.
